      "review_text": "A nice little distraction of a game that will keep you semi busy for some hours, especially if you decide to go for all achievements like me. \r\n\r\nPositives: It has a satisfying loop, I like how getting more automation etc. has been implemented and the sound effects aren't anything too repetitive or annoying to me. Game is also quite cheap and for that there's a surprisingly good amount of things here.\r\n\r\nNegatives: While there is story it doesn't feel to especially wrap itself up or go much anywhere, which is fine for a title of this price range but a bit of a shame. As of writing this review the game also has quite a few bugs in it still, like getting stuck in \"coin mode\" when re-entering your table, unable to scratch other lots or for example lots being thrown all over your sticky mat if you are unveiling a super lot or whatever they were called. However, all bugs I encountered that actually prevented me from proceeding fixed themselves by returning to the main screen and re-entering the game I never lost any progress but was now bug free.",
